        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2021-02-12 06:31:48.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nThis is a topic branch and it's valid only when merged together! Please don't merge single commits in a topic....",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
      {
        "id": "539102179b3ab39b21ab0852d00651ad0836992e",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 4965,
          "name": "Krzysztof Opasiak",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "k.opasiak@samsung.com",
          "username": "kopasiak"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2021-02-16 13:12:07.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n> Patch Set 3:\n> \n> This is a topic branch and it's valid only when merged together! Please don't merge single commits in a topic....\n\nIt's not the way how gerrit works\nIt also violates the basic bisectability principle\nNon of the individual commits in the \"topic\" or any other series should break the master even for a minute",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
      {
        "id": "e16e87b409faa4897d426ab9fb5a7a8b7e880012",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 5097,
          "name": "Bartek Grzybowski",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "b.grzybowski@partner.samsung.com",
          "username": "bgrzybowski"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2021-02-16 13:28:00.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n> Patch Set 3:\n> \n> > Patch Set 3:\n> > \n> > This is a topic branch and it's valid only when merged together! Please don't merge single commits in a topic....\n> \n> It's not the way how gerrit works\n> It also violates the basic bisectability principle\n> Non of the individual commits in the \"topic\" or any other series should break the master even for a minute\n\nCorrect. Unless it's a topic branch (Gerrit's \"topic\" is what \"feature branch\" is in other VCS tools, see https://gerrit-review.googlesource.com/Documentation/intro-user.html#topics -> \"Often changes that together implement a feature or a user story are group by a topic.\") \n\nSo yes, it's perfectly fine if only all changes _together_ introduce fully new functionality as long as each of them passes unit tests (like in case discussed here).\n\nIf some other technique should be used with gerrit to physically disallow merging incomplete feature i'm open to suggestions. I will give a try with a real separate temp feature branch next time.\n\nRef.: https://www.martinfowler.com/bliki/FeatureBranch.html",
        "patchset_number": 3
      }
    ]
